    <note>Cai(1) Hang [10055] The son #2 of Yuanding [10049], who became the heir of his father's maternal elder cousin (wai biao xiong), Yu(4) Ying [10056]. Hang changed his mingzi to Zhifang and became Yu(4) Zhifang [10057]. After recommendation for the exams by the community, he followed his mother's orders and took care of family affairs. He later became Liangzhe yungan. He was the author of the Chunqiu dayi and a follower of the school of Zhu(1) Xi [3257]. CBD, 5, 3782-3783.</note>
